<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Smythe</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 169.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Adverting to your No. 191, of March 2
                            last, and to your No. 204, of April 30, 1896, relative to the expulsion
                            of Hugo O. Loewi from Haiti, I have to say that the promise of the
                            minister for foreign affairs, made in your No. 191, to furnish you with
                            a statement in writing giving the reasons for Mr. Loewi’s expulsion, has
                            never been fulfilled.</p>
                        <p>You are accordingly instructed to request that the promised statement be
                            promptly furnished you for submission to your Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>